tags.description:
Historic site of Native Haudenosaunee Oneida Village (16th century, population: 1,000 to 1,500). Known to themselves as Onyota'a:ka, "the people of the standing stone".
Recognized site of 1615 Champlain-Oneida Battleground (French & Indian wars).
